jects/Intl/DateTimeFormat\"><code>Intl.DateTimeFormat</code></a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/ListFormat\"><code>Intl.ListFormat</code></a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/NumberFormat\"><code>Intl.NumberFormat</code></a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/PluralRules\"><code>Intl.PluralRules</code></a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/Segmenter\"><code>Intl.Segmenter</code></a></strong></li><li><strong>Inheritance:</strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><details><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li></ol></details></li><li><details><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"JSRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code></strong> object enables language-sensitive relative time formatting.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"try_it","title":"Try it","isH3":false,"content":"<iframe class=\"interactive is-js-height\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/intl-relativetimeformat.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/RelativeTimeFormat\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates a new <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"static_methods","title":"Static methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.supportedlocalesof\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/supportedLocalesOf\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.supportedLocalesOf()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns an array containing those of the provided locales that are supported without having to fall back to the runtime's default locale.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p>These properties are defined on <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype</code> and shared by all <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code> instances.</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.prototype.constructor\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype.constructor</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The constructor function that created the instance object. For <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code> instances, the initial value is the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/RelativeTimeFormat\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code></a> constructor.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.prototypetostringtag\"><a href=\"#intl.relativetimeformat.prototypetostringtag\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype[@@toStringTag]</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The initial value of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol/toStringTag\"><code>@@toStringTag</code></a> property is the string <code>\"Intl.RelativeTimeFormat\"</code>. This property is used in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.prototype.format\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/format\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype.format()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Formats a <code>value</code> and a <code>unit</code> according to the locale and formatting options of the given <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.prototype.formattoparts\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/formatToParts\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype.formatToParts()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array\"><code>Array</code></a> of objects representing the relative time format in parts that can be used for custom locale-aware formatting.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"intl.relativetimeformat.prototype.resolvedoptions\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat/resolvedOptions\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat.prototype.resolvedOptions()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a new object with properties reflecting the locale and formatting options computed during initialization of the object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"basic_format_usage","title":"Basic format usage","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The following example shows how to use a relative time formatter for the English language.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Create a relative time formatter in your locale</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// with default values explicitly passed in.</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> rtf <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Intl<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>RelativeTimeFormat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">localeMatcher</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"best fit\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// other values: \"lookup\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">numeric</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"always\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// other values: \"auto\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">style</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"long\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// other values: \"short\" or \"narrow\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Format relative time using negative value (-1).</span>\nrtf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">format</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"day\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// \"1 day ago\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Format relative time using positive value (1).</span>\nrtf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">format</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"day\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// \"in 1 day\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"using_formattoparts","title":"Using formatToParts","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The following example shows how to create a relative time formatter returning formatted parts.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> rtf <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Intl<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>RelativeTimeFormat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">numeric</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"auto\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Format relative time using the day unit.</span>\nrtf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">formatToParts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"day\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [{ type: \"literal\", value: \"yesterday\"}]</span>\n\nrtf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">formatToParts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"day\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">//   { type: \"literal\", value: \"in \" },</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">//   { type: \"integer\", value: \"100\", unit: \"day\" },</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">//   { type: \"literal\", value: \" days\" }</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ]</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://tc39.es/ecma402/#relativetimeformat-objects","title":"ECMAScript Internationalization API Specification"}],"query":"javascript.builtins.Intl.RelativeTimeFormat"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Intl.RelativeTimeFormat"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://formatjs.io/docs/polyfills/intl-relativetimeformat/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Polyfill of <code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code> in FormatJS</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl\"><code>Intl</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://v8.dev/features/intl-relativetimeformat\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\"><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code></a> on v8.dev (2018)</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Try it","id":"try_it"},{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Static methods","id":"static_methods"},{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Intl.RelativeTimeFormat object enables language-sensitive relative time formatting.","popularity":0.0137,"modified":"2023-08-21T07:19:52.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/intl/relativetimeformat","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/intl/relativetimeformat/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/70f09675ddcfc75a3bb66d2dce4cf82738948a37","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"Intl.RelativeTimeFormat","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"Reference"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Standard built-in objects"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl","title":"Intl"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/RelativeTimeFormat","title":"Intl.RelativeTimeFormat"}],"pageTitle":"Intl.RelativeTimeFormat - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}